%N A397765 Number of quintuples (P, I_1, I_2, I_3, I_4) where P is a partially ordered set on n labeled elements and I_1, I_2, I_3, I_4 are order ideals (down-sets) of P; equivalently, sum over labeled posets P on [n] of the fourth power of the number of antichains of P.
%C A397765 a(n) = Sum_{P} d(P)^4 over the A001035(n) labeled posets P on [n], where d(P) is the number of antichains (equivalently order ideals / down-sets) of P. This is the k=4 member of the antichain-count moment family k=1..4 (k=1: A397542) used to compute A001035(19).
%C A397765 a(n) is the number of labeled posets on n+4 elements in which four designated elements are all maximal (with proof: attach a new maximal point above each of the four ideals; maximal points are automatically pairwise incomparable, and the correspondence is a bijection).
%H A397765 Rafael Ayala, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2606.31526">The number of labeled partial orders and topologies on 19 points</a>, arXiv:2606.31526 [math.CO], 2026.
%H A397765 Rafael Ayala, <a href="https://github.com/Rafael-Ayala/posets-and-topologies-19">Code and data for the antichain-count moments</a>
%Y A397765 Cf. A001035 (k=0, number of labeled posets), A397542 (k=1), A395723 (k=2), A397764 (k=3), A000798.
%K A397765 nonn,new
